INSERT INTO `personnel` VALUES (1,1,1,'Mayor',1,'Mayor','cave','carmen','',949,425,2510,'','ccave@cityofalisoviejo.com','Carmen Cave was selected by her colleagues to serve as Mayor during the City Council\'s annual reorganization on Dec. 1, 2010. This is the fourth mayoral stint for Carmen, who is a recognized leader throughout the county for her resolve and commitment to ensuring Aliso Viejo remains a strong and viable community. As the co-founder and former president of the Cityhood Committee, Carmen was successful in bringing a fiscally responsible cityhood plan to voters and was the driving force behind the incorporation drive for Orange County\'s 34th city. In fact, Senator Dick Ackerman honored Carmen for her efforts with the 2008 Woman of the Year Award for the 33rd District.<p>Proudly serving as the City\'s first Mayor upon incorporation on July 1, 2001, Carmen went on to serve as Mayor again in 2006 and 2007. <p>Carmen represents the City of Aliso Viejo as a board member for the San Joaquin Transportation Corridor Agencies (TCA) and Transportation Corridor System and is an alternate board member of Orange County Fire Authority (OCFA). Carmen serves the City on the South OC Major Investment Committee and Aliso Creek Watershed Electeds Coalition. She served as alternate board member for ETRPA (El Toro Reuse Planning Authority) and was the City\'s representative to the Great Park Advisory Council in 2007.<p>The council member brings a wealth of professional experience to the table. She has extensive experience in the social service field; land-use planning; and commercial development. Carmen is currently working as Planning Director for the City of Menifee, which incorporated on Oct. 1, 2008 as Riverside County\'s 26th city.<p>Carmen holds a B.A. degree in English and Psychology, and a Ph.D. in Educational Psychology from Stanford University. <p>A 19-year Aliso Viejo resident, Carmen is a fixture in town, donating her time and efforts to several charities and organizations. She serves as Chair of the Aliso Viejo Community Cup - an annual golf tournament dedicated to raising funds for the City\'s Family Resource Center and other youth programs in Aliso Viejo. Carmen also served on Mission Hospital\'s Latino Leadership Council and was a steering committee member for the YMCA\'s \"OC In Motion\" campaign to promote health and wellness programs for youth.<p>Along with giving back to the community, Carmen enjoys participating in community activities, visiting local parks and trails and is often seen around town with her husband, Duane, and their rescued dogs, \"Gus\" and \"Charlie.\" An avid animal rescuer, Carmen adopted Zephyr, an endangered California Desert Tortoise. Gus was adopted through Pooch Heaven, an animal-rescue group often found at the Aliso Viejo PetSmart. Charlie was adopted through \"Save the Dalmatians & Others\" - another local animal-rescue organization.','official_cave.jpg'),(2,1,1,'Mayor Pro Tem',2,'Mayor Pro Tem','garcia','donald','a.',949,425,2510,'','dgarcia@cityofalisoviejo.com ','Donald Garcia served as Mayor in 2009 and Mayor Pro Tem in 2008. He has served on the council since being appointed by the City Council on March 1, 2007. <p>Donald is a member in good standing with the California State Bar. He has past and/or current affiliations with several professional organizations, which include the Hispanic Bar Association, Orange County Trial Lawyers, the Orange County Bar Association and the Consumer Attorneys of California. Prior to becoming a lawyer, Donald held the position as Vice President of a leading arbitration and mediation company. He has been a practicing attorney for more than 15 years. <p>Donald\'s community involvement and emphasis for keeping a pulse on Aliso Viejo\'s affairs has grown throughout his 17 years in town. In 2000, he was appointed architectural chairman of his neighborhood subdivision. In 2002, he was appointed to the City\'s Development Review Committee (DRC) and served for three years. <p>Donald represents the City as a board member for the Orange County Fire Authority (OCFA). <p>Donald proudly served in the US Army 101st Airborne Division and overseas the City\'s annual Veterans Appreciation Program. He has been married for 17 years and has four children. During his free time, Donald and his lovely wife, Toni, juggle sports with their kids, which includes basketball and baseball with their oldest son; football, basketball and baseball with their youngest son; and volleyball with their daughter. ','official_garcia.jpg'),(3,1,1,'Council Member',3,'Council Member','ficke','greg','',949,425,2510,'','gficke@cityofalisoviejo.com','A founding father of Aliso Viejo, Greg was elected to serve on the City\'s first City Council when Aliso Viejo incorporated on July 1, 2001. He was re-elected in 2004 and was appointed to the post in August 2008 after running unopposed for the four-year term.<p>Greg is a director in Cushman & Wakefield\'s Irvine office, specializing in tenant representation, landlord representation and corporate services. The company is a global commercial real estate service firm. Greg\'s professional career complements his philosophy of the importance of economic vitality and working to attract businesses to Aliso Viejo.<p>Greg represents the City of Aliso Viejo as an alternate board member for the San Joaquin Transportation Corridor Agencies (TCA) and Transportation Corridor System. He serves as chair of the Orange County Library Task Force. The task force is charged with providing library resources to the community and making the library system more functional for residents\' daily lives. Greg is founder and chairman of the Aliso Viejo Business Council and is a member of the South Orange County Regional Chambers of Commerce and Irvine Chamber of Commerce.<p>Greg was passionately and actively involved in the grass-roots efforts to stop an airport at El Toro. Throughout the years, he has continued to contribute time and money to a number of local organizations, charities and worthwhile causes. He has worked with the Boys & Girls Scouts of America, AYSO, American Cancer Society, United Way, AV Little League, Trails4All, and spent time as a CUSD \"Principal for a Day.\"<p>Greg put himself through school and holds a BA in Marketing and a Masters of Business Administration in International Business from California State University, Fullerton. Greg has lived in town for more than 16 years. He has two children who attend local public schools and are involved in an array of community and sports programs. During his free time, Greg enjoys spending quality time with his family and attending community events. He is active in his church and temple.','official_ficke.jpg'),(4,1,1,'Council Member',4,'Council Member','phillips','william','bill',949,425,2510,'','wphillips@cityofalisoviejo.com','Bill Phillips served as the City\'s third Mayor in 2004 since Aliso Viejo\'s July 1, 2001 incorporation. He went on to serve as Mayor again in 2008 and enjoyed leading his weekly \"Walks with the Mayor\" to meet residents, promote fitness and enjoy the City\'s pristine landscape and beauty.<p>Bill works as an urban design consultant throughout Southern California serving both public and private sector clients. Bill has extensive experience in preparing large-scale master/specific plans and urban redevelopment plans. He holds a Bachelor of Architecture degree from Cal Poly, San Luis Obispo and is a graduate of the Leadership Southern California Program.<p>Having lived in Aliso Viejo since 1989, Bill became immersed in the community through his involvement with AVCA (Aliso Viejo Community Association) as a member for both the AVCA Planning Advisory Committee and the AVCA Parks and Recreation Committee. He also was an active member of the Aliso Viejo Cityhood Committee and was appointed to the Orange County Transit Advisory Committee for two years.<p>A member of Saddleback Memorial Medical Center\'s Board of Directors, Bill also spent two years as chairman and served on the Memorial Health Services Board of Directors. Bill\'s professional affiliations include the Urban Land Institute and the American Planning Association. His community activities also include participation as a board member for Saint Mary and All Angels School and as a past participant of the Disney G.O.A.L.S. Program. <p>Representing the City of Aliso Viejo, Bill serves as Director on the Laguna Canyon Foundation Board of Directors and is a member of the Coastal Greenbelt Authority. <p>Bill, along with his wife and their two children, enjoy participating in an array of activities and organizations that involves much of their family time together.','official_phillips.jpg'),(5,1,1,'Council Member',5,'Council Member','tsunoda','phillip','b.',949,425,2510,'','ptsunoda@cityofalisoviejo.com','Phillip B. Tsunoda proudly served as Mayor in 2010 and Mayor Pro Tem in 2009. Phillip was elected by voters in November 2010 and has served the residents of Aliso Viejo since the City Council appointed him to the post in May 2007.<p>Phillip serves as Chief of Staff to the Orange County Board of Supervisors, 4th District Office. Before joining the Chairman\'s staff, he served for three years as the Director of External Affairs for Orange County Clerk-Recorder Tom Daly. From 1997 to 2004, Phillip was the Manager of Government Relations for the City of Anaheim and was responsible for all external governmental affairs for Anaheim including serving as liaison to all levels of government, local, regional, state and federal. <p>Phillip\'s professional background also includes work with County of Orange Health Care Agency, County Board of Supervisors - 2nd District and others. He has a wealth of experience in municipal and regional issues dealing with land-use, transportation and law enforcement-related programs, policies and projects. <p>Phillip represents the City of Aliso Viejo on the Board of Trustees for the Orange County Vector Control District. He also serves as an Alternate on the Transportation Corridor Agency (TCA) - Foothill/Eastern Board of Directors as well as an Alternate on the Orange County Council of Governments Board of Directors. He also serves as an ex-officio member of the Orange County Tourism Council Board of Directors, a position appointed by the Orange County Board of Supervisors.<p>Phillip\'s community involvement has grown throughout his 12 years in town. He was a member of the Aliso Viejo Community Association (AVCA) Planning Committee where he reviewed and recommended planning and development projects. Phillip has also served two terms on the Orange County Transportation Authority\'s Citizen Advisory Committee and is a voting delegate to the AVCA. <p>In September 2007, he was appointed to the Board of Trustees of the South Coast Medical Center Foundation. The Foundation raises monies to purchase much-needed capital equipment for South Coast Medical Center. <p>Phillip has been married for more than 13 years and has two children. During his free time, he enjoys spending time with his family and is involved in his son\'s baseball league - where he currently serves on the Aliso Viejo Little League Board of Directors, working directly with the Aliso Viejo business community to financially assist the League.','official_tsunoda.jpg'),(6,1,4,'City Attorney',7,'Mr.','smith','scott','c.',949,425,2510,'','city-attorney@cityofalisoviejo.com','Bio goes here.','generic_official.jpg'),(7,1,2,'City Manager',6,'Mr.','pulone','mark','a.',949,425,2510,'','city-manager@cityofalisoviejo.com','Bio goes here.','generic_official.jpg'),(8,1,3,'City Clerk',8,'Ms.','ramos','susan','a.',949,425,2505,'','city-clerk@cityofalisoviejo.com','Bio goes here.','generic_official.jpg'),(9,1,5,'Director of Financial Services',9,'Ms.','tharani','gina','m.',949,425,2521,'','finance@cityofalisoviejo.com','Bio goes here.','generic_official.jpg'),(10,1,14,'Director of Administrative Services',10,'Mr.','yas